During World War II, the term assault rifle was coined. However, during the Vietnam era, the M16 was developed. A common misconception of the term "assault rifle" is not properly used. The civilian version of the M16 is known as the AR-15. AR stands for "ArmaLite Rifle," not "Assault Rifle." This is why the term assault rifle is used incorrectly when describing rifles with large-capacity magazines. The AK-47 or "Kalashinkov" became the most widely developed rifle for countries on a global scale.
